-- Hungary Stocks: CIG, Mol, OTP Shares Move in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-04T15:57:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/hungary-stocks-cig-mol-otp-shares-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
fell 0.9 percent to 18,176.78 as of the close in Budapest.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL)  , Hungary’s largest refiner, dropped 1.9
percent to 17,750 forint. Oil futures tumbled after the U.S.
Energy Department said stockpiles rose the most since 2008.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell 0.5
percent to 3,730 forint. Minutes released yesterday from the
March 13 Federal Reserve policy meeting showed it was holding
off on increasing monetary accommodation unless U.S. economic
expansion faltered or prices rose at a rate slower than its 2
percent target.  CIG Pannonia Eletbiztosito Nyrt. (PANNONIA HB), a Hungarian
life insurer, slumped for a fourth day, reaching a record low.
The shares dropped 2.5 percent to 395 forint, the lowest level
since their November 2010 listing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
